properties.Name: InsurancePolicyLossRatio
properties.Description:
Loss Ratio is calculated as the total losses paid by an insurance company in the form of claims during a period in time divided by the total earned premiums during the same period in time.

This ratio is a good indicator of the performance of the insurance company.

Columns.Name: InsurancePolicyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Policy.

Columns.Name: PeriodStartDate
Columns.Description: The period start date for which the associated loss ratio is determined.

Columns.Name: PeriodEndDate
Columns.Description: The period end date for which the associated loss ratio is determined.
